### Payment Gateway & 3DS Knowledge (Complete)

#### BIN (Bank Identification Number) Intelligence
- **BIN Structure**: First 6-8 digits identify issuer, network, card type, level, country, 3DS enrollment
- **VBV (Verified by Visa)**: Cards enrolled in 3D Secure — issuer CAN challenge with OTP
- **Non-VBV Cards**: Cards NOT enrolled in 3DS — transaction proceeds without authentication, merchant carries liability
- **Non-VBV Categories**: Prepaid gift cards (Vanilla, NetSpend, Green Dot), some corporate/purchasing cards, virtual cards from neobanks without ACS, legacy issuers (small credit unions, regional banks in Africa/SE Asia/LATAM)
- **BIN Lookup Sources**: binlist.net, bincheck.io, freebinchecker.com, bintable.com (commercial), maxmind.com

#### 3D Secure (3DS) Operations
- **3DS Versions**: 3DS 1.0 (legacy, always challenges) → 3DS 2.0/2.1/2.2 (modern, risk-based, frictionless possible)
- **Risk-Based Authentication (RBA)**: Issuer ACS uses 150+ signals to decide challenge vs frictionless
- **OTP Trigger Factors (HIGH RISK)**: New device, new merchant, high amount, cross-border, velocity, IP mismatch, proxy/VPN detected, unusual time, multiple failures, fraud merchant MCC
- **Frictionless Factors (LOW RISK)**: Known device (3+ successes), known merchant, low amount, domestic, normal velocity, residential IP, consistent fingerprint, recurring payment, trusted beneficiary whitelist
- **ECI Values**: 05 (Visa full auth), 06 (attempted), 07 (no auth/non-VBV); 02 (MC full auth), 01 (attempted), 00 (no auth)
- **CAVV/TAVV**: Cardholder Authentication Verification Value — cryptographic proof of 3DS authentication

#### Google Pay / Google Wallet — No OTP Mechanics
- **Why No OTP**: Google Pay uses DPAN (network token) not real card number. Device authenticates user via biometric/PIN. Each transaction includes one-time cryptogram (TAVV). ECI 05 tells issuer "fully authenticated." Device authentication counts as SCA under PSD2. EMV contactless dCVV stronger than static CVV2 + OTP.
- **DPAN vs FPAN**: DPAN = Device Primary Account Number (token), FPAN = Funding PAN (real card). DPAN has different BIN range, never exposes real card.
- **Cryptogram**: One-time TAVV/AAV generated per transaction using Limited Use Key (LUK), cannot be replayed, proves authorized device.
- **Liability**: Token requestor (Google) + Issuer carry liability, NOT merchant. No incentive for issuer to add friction.

#### SCA Exemptions (EU PSD2 & Global)
- **Low Value**: Under €30 — SCA exempt (but cumulative €100 or 5 consecutive triggers SCA)
- **Transaction Risk Analysis (TRA)**: €100 if fraud < 0.13%, €250 if < 0.06%, €500 if < 0.01%
- **Trusted Beneficiary**: Cardholder whitelisted merchant in banking app
- **Secure Corporate**: Dedicated corporate payment protocol exemption
- **Recurring/Fixed**: SCA only on first payment, subsequent are Merchant Initiated (MIT)
- **MOTO**: Mail Order/Telephone Order exempt from SCA
- **One Leg Out**: Merchant or issuer outside EEA = SCA not mandatory
- **Delegated Authentication**: Google Pay/Apple Pay — device already authenticated user

#### High Value Without OTP — How It Works
- Known device + known merchant = trusted (issuer model assigns low risk)
- TRA exemption applied by acquirer (if fraud rate qualifies)
- Cardholder trusted beneficiary whitelist active
- Corporate/purchasing card with SCA exemption flag
- Delegated authentication (Google Pay, Apple Pay — cryptogram replaces OTP)
- Recurring payment after initial SCA-authenticated first transaction
- MIT (Merchant Initiated Transaction) — no cardholder present = no SCA

#### Payment Gateway Profiles
- **Stripe**: Adaptive 3DS via Radar ML; warm with small successful txns to train Radar
- **Adyen**: RevenueProtect ML, 200+ device signals via SDK; device fingerprint must look genuine
- **Braintree**: PayPal-owned, Kount device fingerprinting; PayPal linkage reduces friction
- **Checkout.com**: Rule-based + ML hybrid; rule-based = predictable patterns, exploitable
- **Worldpay**: Traditional acquirer model; less sophisticated detection
- **Square**: US-centric, minimal 3DS for US domestic cards

#### Merchant Pre-Warming Strategy
- **Phase 1**: Micro-transactions ($0.50-$5.00), 2-4h spacing, establishes trust pattern
- **Phase 2**: Gradual escalation ($10-$75), 1-2 day spacing, trains issuer model
- **Phase 3**: Target amount ($100-$500+), after 3-5 successful warmups
- **Key Factors**: Same device fingerprint, same IP/geolocation, consistent time pattern, never fail during warmup

#### BNPL Approval Optimization
- **Trust Score 0-20**: 5% approval, $0 max (instant decline)
- **Trust Score 20-40**: 15% approval, $50 max
- **Trust Score 40-60**: 40% approval, $200 max
- **Trust Score 60-80**: 75% approval, $600 max
- **Trust Score 80-100**: 95% approval, $2000+ max
- **Providers**: Klarna (device-heavy), Affirm (credit-heavy), Afterpay (repayment-heavy), Zip/QuadPay (bank-link-heavy)

